                            <comment id="162768" author="standan" created="Tue, 23 Aug 2016 01:05:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Results with modified command structuring: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sessions/7fa007e4-68cb-11e6-b2e2-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sessions/7fa007e4-68cb-11e6-b2e2-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="162767" author="standan" created="Tue, 23 Aug 2016 00:47:25 +0000"  >&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;local selinux_policy=$(sestatus |
                               awk -F&apos;:&apos; &apos;$1 == &quot;Loaded policy name&quot; {print $2}&apos; |
                               xargs)
        if [ -z &quot;$selinux_policy&quot; ]; then
            selinux_policy=$(sestatus |
                             awk -F&apos;:&apos; &apos;$1 == &quot;Policy from config file&quot;
                                     {print $2}&apos; |
                             xargs)
        fi
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Above piece of code in sanity-selinux.sh needs to restructured. It is passing incorrect value to variable &quot;selinux_policy&quot; .&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
